Open Weather API Testing using Postman

1. Test for temperature and city name.
  a. Q parameter, city name = Cluj-Napoca
  b. Appid = Generated API by Open Weather
  c. Units = metric( by default it is set as "standard" which return degree's in Kelvin.
  d. Expected results: Should return the city name as Cluj-Napoca, and temperature mesured in Celsius degrees.
  e. Actual Results: They are posted in https://github.com/tandea/API-Testing/tree/main/Open%20Weather%20Api%20Testing.

2.Steps to reproduce
  a. Copy-paste the URL(https://api.openweathermap.org/data/2.5/weather?q=Cluj-Napoca&appid=cf2bd91098c042062bc06a5f0e936c92&units=metric) into Postman application
  b. Press Send
  c. Results as JSON format https://github.com/tandea/API-Testing/blob/19e0510b20e40cc867e288a57360bfc74d4c6afb/Open%20Weather%20Api%20Testing/postman%20screenshoot.png

3. Checking provided data
  a. City Name = "coord": { 
        "lon": 23.6,
        "lat": 46.7667
    },
    
